# ----- Meta Descriptions -----
meta-desc-home = Offensive security platform with real-time findings. Penetration testing, vulnerability scanning, red teaming, and attack surface mapping. SSO on every plan. From { -currency } 99/mo.
meta-desc-services = Professional penetration testing, red teaming, and vulnerability scanning. Web app, network, API, and cloud security assessments by experienced pentesters. Start testing today.
meta-desc-pricing = Transparent, accessible security testing plans for every EU business. From startup vulnerability scans to enterprise pentesting. No hidden fees. 100% EU-hosted.
meta-desc-about = Built by European security professionals, for European businesses. 100% EU-based, committed to data sovereignty, and obsessed with breaking into systems. Meet our team.
meta-desc-blog = Expert guides on offensive security, penetration testing techniques, red team tactics, and attack surface management. Stay ahead of threats with insights from EU-based security professionals.
meta-desc-contact = Request a tailored penetration testing quote for your EU business. Fast response, transparent pricing, and offensive security from an EU-based team.
meta-desc-redteam = Full-scope red team assessments simulating real-world attackers. Social engineering, network intrusion, and data exfiltration. EU-based team. Data stays in the EU.
meta-desc-attack-surface = Know what attackers see. Continuous attack surface mapping, exposed asset discovery, dark web monitoring, and shadow IT detection. 100% EU-hosted.
meta-desc-portal = Manage your penetration testing engagements from scope to report. Track findings in real time, download audit-ready reports, and collaborate with your pentest team.
meta-desc-request = Define your pentest scope online and receive a tailored offer within hours. Web apps, networks, APIs, cloud — our guided wizard makes scoping simple. 100% EU-hosted.
meta-desc-free-tools = Free online vulnerability scanning and reconnaissance tools. Check your attack surface, discover exposed services, and identify security weaknesses. No signup required.

# ----- Hero Section -----
hero-headline = Your Security. Your Data. Your Europe.
hero-subheadline = Penetration testing and vulnerability scanning built in the EU, hosted in the EU, governed by EU law. Protect your business without compromising on data sovereignty.
hero-cta-primary = Start Free Scan
hero-cta-secondary = View Pricing Plans

# ----- Value Propositions -----
value-prop-sovereignty-title = EU-Sovereign by Design
value-prop-sovereignty-body = Your scan data, results, and reports are processed and stored exclusively within EU borders. No US CLOUD Act exposure. No foreign government access requests. Full alignment with EU data sovereignty requirements.

value-prop-workflow-title = End-to-End Pentest Workflow
value-prop-workflow-body = No more email chains and spreadsheets. Define your scope, receive an offer, track findings in real time, and download audit-ready reports — all from one integrated platform. Every step is structured, traceable, and tied to your organisation.

value-prop-offensive-title = Offensive Security Specialists
value-prop-offensive-body = We think like attackers. Our team combines automated scanning with manual exploitation, social engineering, and red team exercises. We find the vulnerabilities that checklists miss — because real adversaries do not follow checklists either.

value-prop-security-title = Built Secure, Not Just Selling Security
value-prop-security-body = We are a security company and our platform reflects it. Strict tenant isolation, least-privilege access controls, and zero cross-tenant data leakage — by design. Every API call is scoped to your organisation and role. We test our own platform the same way we test yours.

value-prop-pricing-title = From { -currency } 99/Month
value-prop-pricing-body = Enterprise-grade security testing should not require enterprise budgets. Our tiered pricing makes professional penetration testing accessible to every EU business, from solo founders to multinational corporations.

# ----- How It Works -----
how-it-works-headline = From Scope to Secure — All in One Platform
how-it-works-intro = Our end-to-end pentest workflow keeps everything in one place: no email chains, no spreadsheets, no separate reporting tools.

how-it-works-step1-title = Define Your Scope
how-it-works-step1-body = Log in and describe what needs testing. Our guided scope wizard walks you through declaring target systems, IP ranges, domains, testing windows, and exclusions. Everything is tied to your organisation — clean, structured, and auditable from the start.

how-it-works-step2-title = Receive Your Offer
how-it-works-step2-body = Our team reviews your scope and creates a tailored offer with pricing, timeline, and deliverables — delivered directly in your dashboard. No back-and-forth emails. Accept, negotiate, or ask questions in-app.

how-it-works-step3-title = Accept and Engage
how-it-works-step3-body = Accept the offer and your engagement is created instantly. Your dedicated pentest team is assigned and ready to begin within the agreed testing window.

how-it-works-step4-title = Watch Findings Come In
how-it-works-step4-body = During the engagement, your pentesters log findings in real time. Each finding includes a business-level description, technical reproduction steps, impact assessment, remediation recommendation, and a severity rating (Extreme, High, Elevated, Moderate, or Low). You can track progress live from your client dashboard.

how-it-works-step5-title = Download Your Report
how-it-works-step5-body = When testing is complete, all findings compile into a comprehensive, downloadable report with technical detail, severity ratings, and remediation guidance. Ready to share with your team or stakeholders.

how-it-works-cta = See the Platform in Action

# ----- Social Proof -----
social-proof-headline = Trusted by Security-Conscious European Organisations

# ----- Attack Surface Urgency -----
urgency-headline = Your Attack Surface Is Growing Every Day
urgency-body = Every new deployment, every API endpoint, every cloud resource expands your attack surface. Attackers are scanning your infrastructure right now. The question is whether you found the vulnerabilities first.
urgency-cta = Map Your Attack Surface

# ----- Service Names & Taglines -----
service-scanning-name = Automated Vulnerability Scanning
service-scanning-tagline = Continuous visibility into your attack surface.
service-scanning-body = Automated scans discover and assess vulnerabilities across your web applications, APIs, networks, and cloud infrastructure. Our scanners run from EU-based nodes with deep threat detection — misconfigurations, outdated software, exposed services, and more.
service-scanning-best-for = Organisations needing regular, repeatable security checks for continuous visibility into their attack surface.

service-webapp-name = Web Application Penetration Testing
service-webapp-tagline = Find vulnerabilities before attackers do.
service-webapp-body = Thorough testing of your web applications combining automated scanning with manual verification. We test for injection flaws, authentication weaknesses, access control failures, business logic errors, and more — following proven offensive methodology.
service-webapp-best-for = SaaS companies, e-commerce platforms, and any organisation with customer-facing web applications.

service-network-name = Network Penetration Testing
service-network-tagline = Test your perimeter and internal defences.
service-network-body = External and internal network assessments that identify exploitable vulnerabilities in your infrastructure. We probe firewalls, VPNs, servers, and network services — simulating real-world attacker techniques.
service-network-best-for = Organisations with on-premises infrastructure, hybrid environments, or regulatory requirements for network-level testing.

service-cloud-name = Cloud Security Assessment
service-cloud-tagline = Secure your cloud — whether it runs in Frankfurt, Dublin, or Stockholm.
service-cloud-body = Review of your cloud infrastructure configuration and security posture across AWS, Azure, and GCP. We identify misconfigurations, overly permissive IAM policies, exposed storage, and architectural weaknesses.
service-cloud-best-for = Organisations running production workloads in EU cloud regions who need assurance that their cloud is configured securely.

service-api-name = API Security Testing
service-api-tagline = Your APIs are your attack surface. Test them.
service-api-body = Dedicated testing of REST, GraphQL, and SOAP APIs for authentication bypass, injection vulnerabilities, data exposure, rate limiting weaknesses, and API-specific attack vectors.
service-api-best-for = API-first companies, microservices architectures, and organisations exposing APIs to partners or the public.

service-managed-name = Managed Penetration Testing
service-managed-tagline = Professional pentesting, managed end-to-end in one platform.
service-managed-body = Our flagship service. Define your scope through our guided wizard, receive a tailored offer, and track your engagement from kickoff to final report — all within the { -brand-short } platform. No separate tools, no email attachments, no lost findings.
service-managed-best-for = Organisations that need professional, human-led penetration testing with full traceability and detailed technical reporting.

service-redteam-name = Red Team Exercises
service-redteam-tagline = Full-scope adversary simulation. We attack like real threat actors.
service-redteam-body = Objective-based assessments that simulate real-world adversaries targeting your organisation. We chain together social engineering, phishing, physical access testing, and technical exploitation to test your detection and response capabilities end-to-end.

service-redteam-social = Social Engineering Assessments — Phishing, vishing, and pretexting campaigns
service-redteam-physical = Physical Intrusion Testing — Badge cloning, tailgating, and facility access
service-redteam-assumed = Assumed Breach Scenarios — Lateral movement and privilege escalation from an insider position
service-redteam-purple = Purple Team Exercises — Collaborative attack-and-defend sessions with your SOC team

service-redteam-best-for = Mature organisations that want to test their detection, response, and resilience against realistic adversary tactics.

