# Pricing: FAQ
pricing-faq-heading = Frequently Asked Questions

pricing-faq-upgrade-q = Can I upgrade or downgrade my plan at any time?
pricing-faq-upgrade-a = Yes. Upgrades take effect immediately with prorated billing. Downgrades apply at your next renewal date.

pricing-faq-trial-q = Is there a free trial?
pricing-faq-trial-a = Recon and Strike plans include a 14-day free trial. No credit card required. Offensive offers a guided demo with our team.

pricing-faq-data-q = Where is my data stored?
pricing-faq-data-a = All scan data, results, and reports are stored in EU-based data centres. We use infrastructure located in Germany and the Netherlands. Your data never leaves the European Union.

pricing-faq-billing-q = Do you offer discounts for annual billing?
pricing-faq-billing-a = Our listed prices are already annual pricing, which represents the best value. Monthly billing is available on the Strike plan at a 20% premium.

pricing-faq-certs-q = How experienced are your testers?
pricing-faq-certs-a = Our security team consists of seasoned offensive security professionals with deep expertise in web application testing, network penetration, and adversary simulation. Enterprise engagements are led by senior testers with extensive real-world experience.

pricing-faq-engagement-q = How does the managed pentest engagement work?
pricing-faq-engagement-a = You define your scope through our guided in-app wizard (targets, IP ranges, testing windows, exclusions). Our team reviews it and sends you an offer with pricing and timeline — all within the platform. Once you accept, pentesters are assigned and findings appear in your dashboard in real time. When testing is complete, you download a detailed technical report. No emails, no spreadsheets, no separate tools.

pricing-faq-realtime-q = Can I see findings during the pentest, or only at the end?
pricing-faq-realtime-a = You see findings as they are logged. Each finding appears in your client dashboard with a business-level description, technical details, impact assessment, severity rating (Extreme/High/Elevated/Moderate/Low), and remediation recommendation. You do not have to wait for the final report.

pricing-faq-access-q = Who can see my pentest data?
pricing-faq-access-a = Only users within your organisation and the pentesters specifically assigned to your engagement. Our platform enforces strict tenant isolation and least-privilege access controls. Administrators manage engagements but cannot access other organisations' data. We practice the same security principles we test for.

pricing-faq-engagement-pricing-q = How are managed pentest engagements priced?
pricing-faq-engagement-pricing-a = Strike plan subscribers can request managed engagements priced per-engagement based on scope complexity. Enterprise plans include bundled pentest engagements at volume pricing. Automated scanning is always included in your plan subscription.

